        <section class="about-us" id="about-us">
          <h1 class="abtusTitle">About Us</h1>
          <div class="text-box">
            <p>Our platform aims to combat food waste by connecting restaurants with surplus food to NGOs serving those in need. Restaurants, join us in redistributing your excess food to the needy. NGOs, sign up to receive food donations from restaurants of your choosing. Let's work together to make a difference!.</p>
      <div class="text" style="font-size:20px;background-color: #eff6ef; /* dark green */;padding: 20px;border-radius: 10%;font-weight: bold;"><b>
        <h2>#EndFoodWaste</h2>
        <p>
          Our website is an initiative aimed at redistributing unsold and excess food from restaurants to people in need through NGOs, thereby reducing food waste in our society. We invite all restaurants to sign up and share their surplus food with those in need. Similarly, NGOs can register to collect food donations from their preferred restaurants. Let's collaborate to tackle food waste and ensure everyone has access to nutritious meals.</p></b>
      </div>
      <div class="our-focus" style="font-size:20px;background-color:#eff4ef; /* dark green */;padding: 20px;border-radius: 10%;font-weight: bold;"><b>
        <h2>OUR FOCUS:</h2>
        <p>
          As per recent findings, the hospitality sector's food wastage is emerging as a key factor in India's food waste crisis. To combat this, our emphasis is on redirecting surplus and unsold food to vulnerable populations, such as residents of charity homes and beneficiaries of non-profit NGOs, including thousands of underprivileged orphans and elders. Through the #ServeNeedy initiative, we act as a vital intermediary between restaurants and these charitable entities, fostering cooperation to ensure surplus food reaches those most in need.</p></b>

      </div>

    </section>

